üìù **Adding Tasks:**
   - The application is useless without the ability to add new tasks.
   - You will implement an "input mode" to capture text for a new task.
   - When the user presses a key (e.g., 'a' for add), the application will enter input mode.
   - The user will type the task description.
   - Pressing `Enter` will create a new `Task` and add it to the `app.tasks` list.
   - Pressing `Escape` will cancel input mode.

